body:
In our app, we need to calculate the exact bounding box (we call it "visible bounding box" as it should only enclose all visible paths) of an SKPath.
However, in skia, the SKPath.getBounds() method returns a rectangle that encompasses also the control points of curves (e.g. cubic bezier curve), which returns a "wrong" result for our use case.

We filed a bug for this here: https://bugs.chromium.org/p/skia/issues/detail?id=5751

and got the response, that we should consider using SKPathOps "TightBounds"
see: 
    /*\* Set the resulting rectangle to the tight bounds of the path.
    @param path The path measured.
    @param result The tight bounds of the path.
    @return True if the bounds could be computed.
    /
    bool SK_API TightBounds(const SkPath& path, SkRect result);

https://github.com/google/skia/blob/master/include/pathops/SkPathOps.h

The following **skia.fiddle** shows how to use it:
https://fiddle.skia.org/c/5a69132d6477821d124b75d8ec4ee949

Could you bind that to "SKPath" somehow, please?
As it is a static method, I do not know how you'd like to bind it to SkiaSharps API (from a design point of view)
